JOHANNESBURG – Outgoing ANC NEC member, Naledi Pandor says there will be an urgent summit on President Jacob Zuma's announcement on free higher education. She said Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba will also address the issue in his budget speech. READ: Clarification needed on free education funding: Habib "We didn't discuss operationalising of the announcements that have been made by the President because we had assurance from minister Gigaba that there would be a focus on this in the budget speech that will be made in February,”  Pandor said. “We did agree that we will convene through the new NEC an urgent summit....on this higher education finance matter..if there is a waste we must grab it and direct it toward supporting young people." eNCA